"Abstract “Careless clicks can-and do-sink corporate ships,” says Nancy Flynn, Executive Director of The ePolicy Institute and author of email Rules and The ePolicy Handbook. One careless click from UK celebrity Robert Kilroy-Silk's secretary lost him his lucrative job with the BBC, not to mention censure by the Arab League and Commission for Racial Equality, a police investigation into allegations of incitement to racial hatred, and a motion in the House of Commons condemning his racist views."
